Package com.rapidminer.belt.reader

Class MixedRowReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.rapidminer.belt.reader.MixedRowReader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MixedRow
    public final class MixedRowReader
extends java.lang.Object
implements MixedRow
    Buffered row-oriented reader for multiple Columns of different capabilities.

    In its initial state the reader does not point at a valid row. Thus, one must invoke move() at least once before reading values using getNumeric(int), getIndex(int) or getObject(int). Example: 

    
 MixedRowReader reader = Buffers.mixedRowReader(...);
 while(reader.hasRemaining()) {
     reader.move();
     for (int i = 0; i < reader.width(); i++) {
         ... = reader.getNumeric(i);
     }
 }

    Given the column-oriented design of Belt, NumericRowReaders do not perform as well as column readers. Thus, whenever possible the use of NumericReaders, CategoricalReaders and ObjectReaders is preferred. Furthermore, a NumericRowReader, CategoricalRowReader or a ObjectRowReader performs better than a MixedRowReader and should be preferred instead whenever possible.

    Author:
    Michael Knopf, Gisa Meier

      • getNumeric

        public double getNumeric​(int index)
        Returns the numeric value of the this row at the given index. Returns Double.NaN in case there is no numeric value at this index. This method is well-defined for indices zero (including) to MixedRow.width() (excluding).

        This method does not perform any range checks.

        This method does never advance the current row. Before invoking this method, you will have to call move() at least once.

        Specified by:
        getNumeric in interface MixedRow
        Parameters:
        index - the index
        Returns:
        the value of the row at the given index if the value is Column.Capability.NUMERIC_READABLE and Double.NaN otherwise
        See Also:
        move()

      • getIndex

        public int getIndex​(int index)
        Returns the category index value of the this row at the given index if the entry is part of a Column.Category.CATEGORICAL column. Returns 0 in case of a Column.Category.OBJECT column and (int) getNumeric(index) in case of a Column.Category.NUMERIC column. This method is well-defined for indices zero (including) to MixedRow.width() (excluding).

        This method does not perform any range checks.

        This method does never advance the current row. Before invoking this method, you will have to call move() at least once.

        Specified by:
        getIndex in interface MixedRow
        Parameters:
        index - the index
        Returns:
        the category value index of the row at the given index for Column.Category.CATEGORICAL entries
        See Also:
        move()

      • setPosition

        public void setPosition​(int position)
        Sets the reader position to the given row but without loading the data. The next move() loads the data and goes to row position+1. Note that this can invalidate the buffer so that a new buffer is filled for the next move.
        Parameters:
        position - the position where to move
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the given position smaller than -1
